---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="AI Systems Consulting – Marriott Systems"
  description="Personalised AI systems for professionals and businesses across Australia and New Zealand – Claude Code environments, custom skills, knowledge graphs, and automation workflows."
>
  <section class="consult-section container">
    <p class="section-label"><span aria-hidden="true">01 / </span>what we build</p>
    <div class="consult-body">
      <p>
        Marriott Systems builds personalised AI systems for professionals and business owners –
        structured setups that know your work, your clients, and how you operate. Not a chat
        window: a working layer on top of your day.
      </p>
      <p>
        In practice, that means a Claude Code environment built around you – a profile that
        persists across every session, custom shortcuts for the tasks you repeat, a knowledge
        graph that maps your documents and finds connections, and an automation roadmap for
        what to tackle next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="consult-section container">
    <p class="section-label"><span aria-hidden="true">02 / </span>who it's for</p>
    <div class="consult-body">
      <p>
        Professionals who spend too much time on work that should be faster – drafting,
        summarising, researching, preparing. Solo operators and small teams. People who have
        used AI through a browser and want something that actually knows them.
      </p>
      <p>
        Current clients include a barrister and a travel industry consultant, with engagements
        across Australia and New Zealand.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="consult-section container">
    <p class="section-label"><span aria-hidden="true">03 / </span>how it works</p>
    <div class="consult-body">
      <ol class="consult-steps">
        <li class="consult-step">
          <span class="consult-step__num mono">01</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Context</strong> – before anything is built, the engagement starts with how
            you actually work: your tools, your clients, your recurring tasks, and the documents
            you keep returning to. A personalised system is only as good as what it knows.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="consult-step">
          <span class="consult-step__num mono">02</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Build</strong> – one focused session that sets up the full environment:
            profile, rules, skills, and knowledge graph. You leave with a working system.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="consult-step">
          <span class="consult-step__num mono">03</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Check-in</strong> – one week later, a review of what you have actually used,
            tuning what isn't working, and adding what has emerged.
          </div>
        </li>
        <li class="consult-step">
          <span class="consult-step__num mono">04</span>
          <div>
            <strong>Ongoing</strong> – monthly support, new skills as your work evolves, graph
            updates, and advanced automations.
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="consult-section container">
    <p class="section-label"><span aria-hidden="true">04 / </span>flagship build</p>
    <div class="consult-body">
      <p>
        The fullest version of this is
        <a href="https://console.jacobmarriott.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Brain Console</a>
        – a business-wide AI brain with persistent memory, tool execution, and a knowledge layer
        that centralises everything a company knows, wired into the tools it already runs on.
      </p>
      <p>
        Where a personal setup knows one professional, Brain Console knows an entire company –
        the same idea, scaled to a whole business.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="consult-section container">
    <p class="section-label"><span aria-hidden="true">05 / </span>get in touch</p>
    <div class="consult-body">
      <p>
        If this sounds relevant, email
        <a href="mailto:hello@jacobmarriott.com">hello@jacobmarriott.com</a> – a short call
        first is always fine.
      </p>
      <p>
        Running a Brisbane hospitality venue? There is a separate offer for you –
        <a href="/hospitality">websites and operational systems</a>, including a $297
        visibility audit with no call required.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .consult-section {
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-8);
  }

  .consult-section:first-of-type {
    border-top: 0;
    padding-top: clamp(5rem, 3rem + 8vw, 9rem);
  }

  .consult-body {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 58ch;
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-prose);
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .consult-body p {
    max-width: none;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .consult-steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .consult-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .consult-step__num {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 0.4em;
  }

  .consult-step div {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-prose);
  }

  .consult-step strong {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (min-width: 48rem) {
    .consult-body {
      padding-left: clamp(0rem, -2rem + 10vw, 8rem);
    }
  }
</style>
